# TypeScript & React Standards

## Components

- Functional components only; use explicit prop interfaces
- Colocate component logic; extract hooks only when reused across files
- Prefer controlled inputs with typed handlers (see `TripForm.tsx`)

## Types

- Shared domain types live in `src/types.ts`
- Validation schemas live in `src/validation.ts` (Zod) — reuse instead of duplicating checks
- Avoid `any`; use `unknown` + narrowing in catch blocks

## State & Persistence

- Trip state shape is `TripBudget`; persist via `localStorage.setItem("aistudio_moto_trips", ...)`
- Use `crypto.randomUUID()` for new trip IDs (never `Math.random` alone)

## API Calls

- Client calls only `/api/gemini/analyze` — send the validated field subset, not the full trip object with extras
- Handle non-OK responses with user-friendly messages; don't surface raw server errors

## Error Handling

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — generic user message, log details
catch (error: unknown) {
  console.error("Context:", error);
  setError("Something went wrong. Please try again.");
}
```
